# pattern applied

@pattern host-aware candidate fleet, mirrors kick_tree.hexa (4345b75f) + hive_parent_sid.hexa (d80a12e8):
  ```
  fn _nexus_root() -> string {
      let n = env("NEXUS")
      if n.len() > 0 { return n }
      let home = env("HOME")
      let candidates = [home + "/core/nexus", home + "/Dev/nexus",
                        "/root/Dev/nexus", "/home/nexus"]
      let mut i = 0
      while i < len(candidates) {
          if file_exists(candidates[i] + "/cli/run.hexa") { return candidates[i] }
          i = i + 1
      }
      return home + "/core/nexus"
  }
  ```
@marker /cli/run.hexa — same marker used by kick_tree + hive_parent_sid.
@helper_choice files without explicit `_file_exists` use the built-in `file_exists()`; kick_dispatch + kick_bench + engine_sync keep their `_file_exists` shell wrappers.

@module_const_variant for module-level constants the cascade is hoisted into a `_resolve_nexus_root()` helper executed once at module init; result bound to the existing NEXUS_ROOT name.

@proposal_archive_variant pre-existing env-override-then-fallback structure preserved; only the literal-only fallback is replaced with the candidate fleet.

